@The Archangel I've been there. As soon as a girl breaks up with you out of nowhere and says she "doesn't want to see you suffer", that's when you know she's been doing something that she knows is bad, but chose that something (or someone) over you. I still remember when my first girlfriend refused to wear the promise ring that I gave her, claiming that she was "allergic to silver" and would get rashes. Being young and naïve, I believed it. I chose to trust her smile as she thanked me and told me how happy she was with the ring. Fast-forward a few months and I hear the same words your ex said to you, that she didn't want to see me suffer. It turns out the girl never got out of her relationship with a certain guy. The whole time I was just being used to "comfort" her while the two of them had a falling out, then I was eventually discarded. I'm cringing at myself for sharing this here, but I think it serves to show how common this kind of stuff is. Plenty of sharks in the sea.
